Title: A CUP OF CHAI
Author: Penova Test

INT. MUMBAI TEA STALL - DAY

Steam rises from a battered kettle. RAJA (50s, weathered) wipes a glass with a corner of his shirt. A radio crackles cricket commentary.

PRIYA (20s, backpack, headphones around her neck) approaches the counter, breathless.

PRIYA
One chai. Extra strong.

RAJA
(without looking up)
Strong like pichhle baar?

PRIYA
Stronger.

Raja smiles, just a flicker, and reaches for the milk.

RAJA
That bad?

PRIYA
The interview was an hour ago. They asked me where I see myself in five years.

RAJA
(pouring)
Ek hi jagah - kahin pe bhi.

PRIYA
That's what I said.

RAJA
And?

PRIYA
They laughed.

Raja sets the steel cup down. The steam curls between them.

RAJA
Then they didn't deserve the answer.

CUT TO:

EXT. STREET OUTSIDE STALL - CONTINUOUS

Priya cradles the cup with both hands. Traffic rushes past. She closes her eyes for one long second, then opens them.

PRIYA
(to no one)
Okay.

She walks off, cup steaming.

FADE OUT.
